      • buildProgressBar

        public String buildProgressBar(int width,
                               String incomplete,
                               String complete,
                               long currentValue,
                               long maxValue)
        Returns a progress bar in String.

        buildProgressBar(10, #, *, 6, 10) will return .

        Same as buildProgressBar(int, String, String, double).

        Parameters:
        width - the width of the progress bar
        incomplete - the text placed when your representative percentage is incomplete
        complete - the text placed when your representative percentage is completed
        currentValue - the progress value
        maxValue - the highest possible value
        Returns:
        the progress bar string
        See Also:
        buildProgressBar(int, String, String, double)

        public String forceColor(String text)

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        the forced text
